Description:
The possibilities are endless on 615m2
Nestled in a fantastic pocket in central Cranbourne sits this lovely 4 bedroom home offering generous living space as well as a convenient lifestyle. On approximately 615m2 this home is perfectly suited to anyone looking to secure their first home, investors search for one with a great location or those looking for a little more space.
Features include:
- Huge light filled Master bedroom with A/C unit, two BIR's and an en-suite.
- Three more generous bedrooms two with built in robes.
- Neutral kitchen with ample cupboard and bench space PLUS gas cooktop.
- Two massive separate living areas to enjoy one showcasing fantastic hardwood floors.
- Double car garage plus secure gated side driveway for ease of storing all those extras.
- Decent backyard for the kids and pets to play.
- Further features include: split system heating and cooling, vertical gas heater, large driveway for extra parking plus loads more.
Ideally located in central Cranbourne the home within walking distance to Cranbourne train station, multiple bus stops, Normanby and Latrobe Street reserves as well as the Hunt Club Shopping Village and Cranbourne Park Shopping Centre. Cranbourne Park Secondary college is also a stone throw away plus the home is on the doorstep of all Cranbourne has to offer including Casey RACE pool and gym, sports and medical facilties do not miss out on this one!

Description:
Nest or Invest 660sqm block
Well established on a huge 660sqm block, this solid 3 bedroom home will provide a great return to an investor while offering a great opportunity to build a unit at the rear (S.T.C.A), or could simply suit a first home buyer.
An approval for second cross over has been granted to have a separate garage/shed or to allow proper duplex/dual occupancy designs in future. The property features 3 great size bedrooms with built in robes , central bathroom and separate toilet , lots of extras including wall heater, formal lounge with timber floors, kitchen with gas cooking, great outdoor entertaining area , formal and informal living areas ,large shed and a huge back yard.
Perfectly positioned within close reach of all that central Cranbourne has to offer is this exciting opportunity that is sure to appeal to those wanting to enter the market, investors or land developers. The central area of Cranbourne is one of the most established and sought-after areas.
Located within walking distance to all facilities, including Cranbourne Park Shopping Centre, local schools including Cranbourne Secondary College and Cranbourne Train Station. This gem is a certain addition to your inspection list.
Be quick to enquire not to miss this opportunity.
ONLY one thing left to do...

Description:
Ex-Display Home Designed for Lifestyle Living
Designed to impress this quality built Carlisle homes showcases a stunning blend of comfort and style boasting many luxury inclusions one could only dream about when purchasing an ex-display show unit.
Oversized timber pivot door grants entry to the home’s formal living area, complete with floor to ceiling tiles and external water feature & pond. The spacious open plan kitchen boats stone benchtops and walk in pantry, the additional 3 living spaces at the rear comprises of a media room featuring built in wall speakers, family area with built in gas fireplace and large meals/dining, all surrounding a covered alfresco area accessible via 2 bolding doors embracing the best of indoor/outdoor living. Manicured gardens and the homes 2nd water feature surrounds the large decked sunbed awaiting those warm summer nights. The home comes complete with, zoned ducted reverse cycle a/c & heating, water tank and is NBN ready.
Offering four bedrooms, two bath with an additional powder room; the master comes with an exceptionally large ensuite with separate toilet, dual vanities, spa bath and overhead ceiling shower and of, an elaborate walk in wardrobe. The double sized garage contains home office cabinets, can be change to an office/workshop STCA.
Within moments to some of cranbourne finest shopping precincts such as Thompson’s shopping centre, Springhill shopping centre, Cranbourne Home. Easy access to both South Gippy & Narre Warren Road with only a 3.5km drive Merinda Park Train Station the home offers flexible transport options whilst also having an abundance of local’s schools nearby.
Deposit terms: 10% of the purchase price.
Preferred Settlement: 30/45/60 days.
An inspection is highly recommended.
*Please note that photo I.D. is required at the time of inspection.
*All information contained herein is gathered from relevant third party sources. We cannot guarantee or give any warranty about the information provided. Interested parties must rely solely on their own enquiries

Description:
**SOLD BY PAUL RINGERI**
CRANBOURNE: **NO BODY CORPORATE FEES APPLICABLE / ALL DAMAGED FENCING WILL BE FIXED UPON SETTLEMENT**
With its quiet court position, the added privacy of being the 2nd unit on a block of only 2 and with easy access to every amenity you could possibly require this unit is a must to inspect!
Presented in A1 condition the property itself has been very well maintained over the years, is full of natural light and is nestled on a sensational parcel of land. With a northerly aspect the block measures a healthy app. 409m2 and is surely of the major selling attractions!
Perfectly suited to owner occupiers and investors, the home features a central hallway that leads to the open plan living/dining area complete with gas heating. The pristine kitchen features an upright oven/stove.
There are 2 robed bedrooms that both offer built in wardrobes, the master also has ensuite style access to the dual entry family bathroom with separate toilet.
Step outside and be greeted by a private driveway that leads to the single carport.
If you believe in the age old theory that good real estate revolves around a central location then you won't be disappointed! Within moments of the shopping facilities situated at the recently revamped Cranbourne Park shopping centre you also have easy access to South Gippsland Highway. Those that don't drive can take full advantage of the public transport leading to the main street and, most importantly, the Cranbourne train station. You are also only a brisk walk from Cranbourne Park primary school and local parkland!
This is bound to walk out the door so don't delay!

In close proximity to great childcares, schools, public transport and the Springhill Shopping Centre, yet tucked away in a quiet location, eager buyers simply should not miss the opportunity to view this property before its sold.
Features include:
- Four spacious bedrooms / three bedrooms or study, with master bedroom with its own walk in robe and en-suite

- Property is fully landscaped

With easy access to M1 freeway and Eastlink with train stations Merinda Park and Cranbourne so close please contact Victor Villella on 0412 437 064 for further information or to arrange a time to view the property.

Description:
" MUST SELL THIS WEEKEND "
The Most Affordable Home in this area. Situated in a secure court location away from the hustle and bustle, amidst fantastic amenities, this home's grand display of features would amaze the most astute buyer. Positioned on 567sqm approx., this home features 4 spacious bedrooms including the master with ensuite, a large kitchen overlooking the open plan meals, an expansive formal lounge, a double garage with automatic shutters and rear access.
The excellent floor plan maximises the use of light throughout the home and the spacious out door area with facility for a gazebo leading into the backyard makes a perfect home for those fulfilled family times with kids and pets. To seal the deal is generous parking space for up to 6 cars including the side access for a boat or trailer.
Other features include
* Ducted heating and evaporative cooling
* Down lights
* Large Laundry with good storage.
* Side access for bins

* Clothes line and more...
Are you looking for a good sized home with space for the whole family? Yeah, this property is for you and it's located within minutes to schools, parks, public transport, Springhill Shopping Centre, Thompsons Parkway Shopping Centre and has easy access to the Monash freeway.
For those on a Budget this home is BIG YES.
